commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1486 - Remove support for some options from !DALSWAVEFORM

Issue description:
The customer had observed that there was no output when using
AT!DALSWAVEFORM=0 i.e. 1 MHz offset CW (Carrier Wave) option which
was supported as per the AT command document.
And on testing the option 3 i.e. LTE PRACH (Physical Random Access
Channel) as well the module crashed after some time.

Root cause:
When this was checked with Qualcomm, they mentioned that the options
0/3/4/5 are not supported on 9615 chipset.

Solution:
Return an error for the unsupported options 0/3/4/5. Made changes
for the solution to be similar to QTI9X07TX-2849.

Resolves: QTI9X1555-1486
Change-Id: Ie8eb37a16b05e38ac118cb806720099fa14876bb
Signed-off-by: infosys_ATMAINT <infosys_ATMAINT@sierrawireless.com>

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1277 - Fix klocwork null pointers dereference errors

Description: During klocwork analysis of commit 31353, this issue
was indicated as critical. During data connected state, this is used
to make HTTP request for assisted positioning.The function parses the
http get request in two carrier specific modes: sprint/non-sprint.
Since the get request on sprint carrier does not require certain fields as
manufacturer, chipset, model, software release, the pointer to these
fields are not assigned valid string after being initialized as NULL.
Even though the nvcarrierget uses a cached value and its value is not
bound to change during scope of the affected function it still does
not guarantee that.

Resolves: QTI9X1555-1277
Change-Id: I632480f001d38f48ab04ab07373e2e13937cdac1
Signed-off-by: Haris Mehmood <HMehmood@sierrawireless.com>
commits.subject: QTI9X1555-1277 - Fix klocwork null pointers dereference errors

QTI9X1555-1473 - AUTO-SIM does not work when SPRINT is active and ATT SIM card

Issue Description:
-----------------
-AUTO-SIM does not work when SPRINT is active and ATT SIM card is present

Root Cause:
----------
-Firmware switch is not working because firmware is not handling the for ICCID
 event. Firmware is performing image switch when SIM status becomes ready
 while with active SPRINT firmware ATT SIM doesn't gets READY state that makes
 firmware switch failure. So we should add the switch case for ICCID and IMSI
 as well along with SIM_READY.

Solution:
---------
-We have made changes in iwsw_sim.c, under imsw_sim_status_notify().

Testing:
--------
-Please refer JIRA for Test logs.

Resolves: QTI9X1555-1473
Change-Id: If206ce2b8af19b7fd6375383d3a3421053629407
Signed-off-by: infosys_atmaint <infosys_atmaint@sierrawireless.com>

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-338 - Enable TX_ON signal at any TX level

Issue:
The TX_ON signal was implemented using Qualcomm's GSM Power Indicator
(GTR_THRESH) method.  This method requires power thresholds applied per
RAT.  As the WP design is to assert TX_ON at minimum power levels,
calibration-specific minimums made it very difficult to configure the
device.

Solution:
Replace the power threshold method with simple GRFC control from the TX
signal tables.  When TX is enabled, the TX_ON signal is asserted, at any
TX power, as expected.

Limitation:
TX_ON is always enabled for this WP series.  The WP76xx/77xx has a control
item for this feature, and as this change is backported from that product
line, the controlling functions are ported in place.  A simpler change would
be to configure the signals directly in the TX tables, but this port allows
future control to be added, if necessary.  The WP76xx/77xx TX_ON signal is
dependant on customization "TXONINDICATION".

Change-Id: Ia9a9fc49a90689c3418492d6b0636853917813bf

Issue Description:
-----------------
Galileo satellites are not displayed in nmea sentences and
AT!GPSSATINFO command response.

----------
-For issue related to NMEA sentences.
In code while defining the TM_CORE_OUTPUT_NMEA_GAGSV, there is small

Qualcomm manages gnss types as (GPS(0), GLO(1), BDS(2), GAL(3)) at

update from Qualcomm for GAL(3), it is missed because SWI handles the
values upto gnss type 2.

---------
-In defination of TM_CORE_OUTPUT_NMEA_GAGSV, gpgsv should be replaced
by gagsv.
-To solve the AT!GPSSATINFO issue BDSSAT should also be added in the
enum for gnss type at swi side.

--------

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1146 - GPS Notifications interfering with asynchronous AT commands

Issue Description:
Module crashes on issuing asynchronous AT commands while GPS data
is being streamed over NMEA port.

Root Cause:
From QTI9X30-2334:
The atgps event handler (atgpseventhandler()) is now being used as a
general GPS event handler for all clients, not just atgps.  It was
using ds_put_cmd() to cause the atgps asynchronous command completion
handler (dsat_swi_atgps_async_event_handler()) to be called,
regardless of whether or not an atgps command was in progress.  The
command completion handler was then being used to send unsolicited
data to the AT port.

The async AT command framework of the DS module expects a completion
call to be matched to the currently blocked AT command, as it should
be.  Calling ds_put_cmd() out of turn was causing the mmgsdi module to
abort when an async command was unexpectedly completed by the atgps
module

Solution:
Port the fix from QTI9X30-2334.

Test Results:
Please refer Jira for test results.

Resolves: QTI9X1555-1146
Change-Id: I9731d8f4de65f9e0709e119eb81cc203d83a4459
Signed-off-by: LKMThiy <LKMThiy@sierrawireless.com>

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1308 - Reset FUMO state to Ready if OMA-DM is not supported

Description: During AVC 2.0 -> AVC 2.0 update process, it was noticed
that the modem will reject legato's QMI_FDT_OPEN_REQ with error
"workspace in use". Currently modem maintains internal FUMO state based
on workspace header bits (first 4 bytes of SSP) and QMI_FDT_STATE based
on nv item used to send/recv indications to/from legato. First upgrade
from AVC 2.0 -> AVC 2.0 is successful due to state clearing by previous
al task.The bootloader will update the status bits based on upgrade status.
Current Reset conditions of this state involves looking at the IDS_RESET_COUNTER
first byte updated by fumoprocstate (not used after AVC 1.0) and QMI_FDT_READY value.
If the QMI_FDT_STATE nv item does not exist on the modem side, this will cause
the failure of the workspace state initialization in idstask for all cases where
OMA-DM is not supported. Since, the FUMO_STATE is retrieved from flash, this
value never resets and all FOTA upgrade fails.

Solution: Modem can not be FUMO UPDATED state during ids task initialization if
OMA-DM is not supported. It must be reset back to ready state.

Testing: Evidence attached on JIRA.
Create two bundles: Release 16 RC5-prime & Release 16 RC3-prime based on the
current modem change.
1. Upgrade Release 15 -> Release 16 RC5-prime
2. Downgrade Release 16 RC5-prime -> Release 16 RC3-prime
3. Upgrade Release 16 RC3-prime -> Release 16 RC5-prime
Repeat several times, check if the state is only reset for AVC 2.0 agent.
Check the final fumo state in QXDM logs.

Resolves: QTI9X1555-1308

Change-Id: I958bf0015734b471f785d3c83ff7eb2c75b9740f
Signed-off-by: Haris Mehmood <HMehmood@sierrawireless.com>

In AVC 2.0, legato uses QMI_DMS_GET_DEV_REVISION_ID_REQ_V01 message which reads the NV item NVPRIID, this exists in the format PART_NUM0x0y and set through PRI common tab in excel.Thus no processing is required in that case.

Since the AVC 1.0 client will only be active for the first upgrade from Rel 15 --> Rel 16, the customer PRIs in that case are bounded to have first digit 0. Afterwards AVC 2.0 would be used.

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1278 - Stuck in LPM after interrupted Image Switch

In rare scenarios devices have been found to be stuck in LPM with an image
mismatch, noted in the AT!IMPREF? response, after a failed FW update attempt.
In these cases the customization GOBIIMEN was also unexpectedly unset, and
other config items from the PRI or expected to be persistent from customer
usage were also unset.

Code inspection revealed that the GOBIIMEN customization was mistakenly used
to gate the application of a new image.  Though not proven, it is suspected
that in these cases the image switch was interrupted by a power cycle or other
failure while the customization had been wiped out but not yet restored.  Of
the logic gates for applying an image, only GOBIIMEN would default to FALSE
after being cleared.  After removing this logic, the mismatch will be detected
and the failed image upgrade will be restarted.

GOBIIMEN is intended to be provided to the host platform to determine whether
or not to provide APIs for Image Switching.  It is not intended to prevent an
image stored on the device from being applied.

Change-Id: I75e809445e1c4951beb250f38e31deb4fbadefbc
commits.subject: QTI9X1555-1278 - Stuck in LPM after interrupted Image Switch

at!antsel?

BAND 1: 0, 1, 1, 2
OK
at!antsel=2,1,0,1,1
OK

BAND 1: 0, 1, 1, 2

Issue Description
le_sim_OpenLogicalChannel()  Can't open a logical channel
QMI_UIM_OPEN_LOGICAL_CHANNEL_REQ_V01 failed

Root cause:
1. timeout in opening logical channel with QMI.
This is a QCT bug. if condition in mmgsdi_uim_uicc_open_channel()
function where due to second condition the open session is getting
return and no manage channel request sent to driver
if (mmgsdi_status != MMGSDI_SUCCESS || extra_param_ptr == NULL)
{ .... }

2.fail to switch sim profile with QMI
As the definition in ETSI102221 10.1.2, the CLA of the below APDU
command can only set to 0x80,
It means the logical channel should be set to 0
Command CLA INS
TERMINAL PROFILE '80' '10'
ENVELOPE '80' 'C2'
FETCH '80' '12'
TERMINAL RESPONSE '80' '14'
SUSPEND UICC '80' '76'

Solution
1.Change the condition in mmgsdi_uim_uicc_open_channel() function to
if (mmgsdi_status != MMGSDI_SUCCESS) { .... }
2.force the APDU command
(FETCH/ENVELOPE/TERMINAL PROFILE/TERMINAL RESPONSE/SUSPEND UICC) send
on channel 0

Note: Changes are ported from -QTI9X1555AR-1798- and -QTI9X40-2102-

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1266 - Implement Fail-safe Disabling of AVC1 by AVC2

Issue Description:
There could be a scenario where AVC1 is unable to complete a FOTA operation on reboot
after a firmware update. The present implementation rejects attempts by AVC2 to disable
AVC1 while AVC1 is attempting to connect to the server, and this situation could
persist indefinitely.

Root Cause
There is no override mechanism that allows AVC2 to disable AVC1

Solution:
AVC1 is given 400s from startup to block AVC2 and complete its FOTA operation. At the
end of that period, AVC1 will accept disable requests by AVC2 regardless of its state
and switch to an initial state.

Testing:
1. Checked that FOTA with AVC1 still works
2. Checked that AVC2 is able to disable AVC1 after AVC1 completes FOTA
3. Checked that AVC2 is still the active LWM2M client after reboot

Change-Id: Ia34d9cf2904de6f606b4069b307ee69cbfde29f5

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1144 - [GNSS] xtra download failed

Issue Description:
GPS XTRA data status is still invalid after executing AT!GPSXTRAINITDNLD

Root Cause:
XTRA client uses a flag to indicate when a download is pending. If the
status is queried using AT!GPSXTRASTATUS?, the flag will be cleared
prematurely and the download will not complete.

There also seems to be conflicts between Qualcomm and Sierra code within
the XTRA client. Sierra code has been added to handle XTRA time and data
events, but the Qualcomm handlers haven't been removed. Executing
both breaks the internal state of the XTRA client, causing errors when
reading in the SNTP response during GPS XTRA time injection.

Solution:
Do not clear the download pending flag when AT!GPSXTRASTATUS is issued,
and remove the Qualcomm handlers for XTRA data and time events to
prevent a conflict with Sierra code.

Testing:

AT!GPSXTRAINITDNLD
OK

Wait 30s

Before:
at!gpsxtrastatus?
 Xtra Time status   = Valid
 Xtra Data status   = Invalid
    Validity Start = 1980 01 06 6 00:00:00
    Validity End   = 1980 01 06 6 00:00:00

OK

After:
at!gpsxtrastatus?
 Xtra Time status   = Valid
 Xtra Data status   = Valid
    Validity Start = 2018 06 08 4 23:00:00
    Validity End   = 2018 06 15 4 23:00:00

OK

Change-Id: If14959a5a77d20f25a5b8ad7cb75411ea0fb7bba
Signed-off-by: Mitchell Nichols <MNichols@sierrawireless.com>

Issue Description:

responses from external clients in the cases that the response is too long to

commits.commitMessage:
QTI9X1555-1260 - WP7504 ANT_CNTL not being set correctly for WCDMA

Issue description:
------------------
After the module has registered to the network and the RF devices
are in sleep mode then the ANT_CNTL signals are not correctly
reflected.

Root Cause:
-----------
After attach the RF devices are put to sleep. But on wake up
if optimization is enabled the rfc signals related to rx band
configuration is not set and hence the GPIO state do not change.

Solution:
---------
Set the rfc signals on wake-up related to rx band configuration
irrespective of if the optimization is enabled or not.

Testing:
--------
Tested if the RF device is not in sleep ANT_CNTL signals are
set appropriately.
- For detailed Test logs please refer JIRA.
